Here is a simple implementation of a vending machine in Java. This program uses object-oriented principles and includes classes for the VendingMachine, Product, and Main (for testing).

```java
import java.util.*;

class Product {
    private String name;
    private double price;

    public Product(String name, double price) {
        this.name = name;
        this.price = price;
    }

    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }

    public double getPrice() {
        return price;
    }
}

class VendingMachine {
    private Map<String, Product> products;
    private double money;

    public VendingMachine() {
        products = new HashMap<>();
        money = 0.0;
    }

    public void addProduct(Product product) {
        products.put(product.getName(), product);
    }

    public void removeProduct(String productName) {
        products.remove(productName);
    }

    public void insertMoney(double amount) {
        money += amount;
    }

    public boolean purchaseProduct(String productName) {
        if(products.containsKey(productName)) {
            Product product = products.get(productName);
            if(money >= product.getPrice()) {
                money -= product.getPrice();
                System.out.println("Purchased " + product.getName());
                return true;
            } else {
                System.out.println("Insufficient funds to purchase " + product.getName());
            }
        } else {
            System.out.println("Product not found");
        }
        return false;
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        VendingMachine vm = new VendingMachine();

        // Add products
        vm.addProduct(new Product("Coke", 1.5));
        vm.addProduct(new Product("Chips", 2.0));

        // Insert money
        vm.insertMoney(3.0);

        // Attempt to purchase
        vm.purchaseProduct("Coke"); // Should succeed
        vm.purchaseProduct("Chips"); // Should fail due to insufficient funds

        // Remove a product
        vm.removeProduct("Coke");

        // Attempt to purchase removed product
        vm.purchaseProduct("Coke"); // Should fail because product was removed
    }
}
```

In this code, `Product` represents an item that can be purchased from the vending machine with a name and price. The `VendingMachine` maintains a list of these products and keeps track of how much money has been inserted. It provides methods to add and remove products, insert money, and purchase products.

The `Main` class tests the functionality of the `VendingMachine`. It creates a vending machine, adds some products, inserts some money, attempts to make purchases, removes a product, and then tries to purchase the removed product.

