```

Next, install the necessary packages by running:

```
npm install express body-parser
```

2. Create an `app.js` file

Create a new file named `app.js` in your project directory. This will be the main entry point for your application.

3. Set up the Express server

Open the `app.js` file and add the following code to set up the Express server:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
